parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Shifter Control Arm and Shaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter control arm and shaft can cause the rider to lose control of the motorcycle, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The shifter control arm and shaft come loose or fall off
making it difficult or impossible to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition lock can cause the saddlebags to malfunction, leading to inconvenience and potential security issues.
symptoms: The ignition lock breaks
the saddlebag lock jams
the saddlebag lid does not seal
the strike plate comes off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The pitting of the rear rocker cover can lead to engine damage and potentially cause oil leaks.
symptoms: The rear rocker cover is pitted
oil leaks may occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the digital oil dipstick can cause inaccurate oil level readings, leading to potential engine damage.
symptoms: The digital oil dipstick blows out
inaccurate oil level readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when coming to a stop after a long drive
the vehicle stalls frequently
the engine dies without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak onto the brakes can cause the brakes to slip, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Oil is leaking onto the brakes
the brakes are slipping
the vehicle is hard to stop
the brakes are making a grinding or screeching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Cutting Out on 1999-2001 Harley-Davidson Cruiser Models with MM EFI System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and cutting out of the engine while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injury or death to the rider.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts out while driving
the bike dies suddenly
the tires lock up
the bike becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the rear tire rim can lead to a sudden loss of tire pressure, causing loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Cracks or fractures in the rear tire rim
often without prior warning or noticeable differences in vehicle handling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The instability of the front end can cause the vehicle to wander or drift, making it difficult to control, especially at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle feels unstable
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially at high speeds
the vehicle's front end feels wobbly or unsteady.
